 The project has been initialized as a React TypeScript library with the following setup:

   - Build Tool: Vite configured in library mode for ESM and UMD outputs.
   - Language: TypeScript with full type generation (vite-plugin-dts).
   - Core Component: C2paManifest for displaying C2PA JSON data.
   - Project Metadata: package.json configured for NPM publishing with proper entry points.
   - Documentation: README.md with usage instructions.
   - Source Control: Git initialized with initial commit and .gitignore.

  You can now start developing your components in src/components/ and build the library using npm run build.

  To publish to NPM:
   1. Ensure you have an NPM account.
   2. Run npm login.
   3. Run npm publish.

  To push to GitHub:
   1. Create a new repository on GitHub.
   2. Run git remote add origin https://github.com/matthewrappard/c2pa-react-component.git.
   3. Run git push -u origin main.